        "timestamp": "2020-12-08 20:42:30.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 6: Code-Review+2\n\nif you passed in \"python2\" or \"python3\" as an argument to build_wagons(), you could have a single function, just add\n\n-p \"$1\"\n\nto the virtualenv call.\n\nWagon can build wagon files that can be used with both python2 and python3 by adding to the wagon command\n\n--pyver 2 --pyver 3\n\n\nIn the brave new world of python3, we should be using pip3 instead of pip. (However, not all linux boxes installed things the python-recommended way, so pip may indeed be the proper thing to use in this environment.)",
        "patchset_number": 6
      },
